📝 How to Use the Database
📊 Reporting & Queries
You can build queries to:
- Track inventory by category or condition
- Monitor low-stock items using Reorder_Threshold
- View distribution history by location or method
- Analyze donor impact and item sourcing


➕ Add a Donor
INSERT INTO Donor (
  donor_id, donor_firstname, donor_lastname, donoation_type,
  donoation_item, donation_date, donor_phone, donor_email
)
VALUES (
  1, 'Jane', 'Doe', 'Food', 'Canned Beans',
  NOW(), '808-555-1234', 'jane@example.com'
);



📦 Add an Item to Inventory
INSERT INTO Item (
  item_id, item_name, item_category, item_qty,
  source_type, item_condition, donor_id, is_kit
)
VALUES (
  101, 'Toothbrush', 'Hygiene', 50,
  'Donated', 'Good', 1, FALSE
);



🛒 Log a Purchase
INSERT INTO Purchase (
  purchase_id, invoice_number, purchase_date,
  purchase_total, vendor_name
)
VALUES (
  201, 'INV-2025-001', '2025-08-27', 125.00, 'Maui Supply Co.'
);


Link the item to the purchase:
INSERT INTO Item_Purchase (item_id, purchase_id)
VALUES (101, 201);



📉 Set Reorder Threshold
INSERT INTO Reorder_Threshold (item_id, min_quantity)
VALUES (101, 20);



📋 Add to Order List
INSERT INTO Order_List (
  order_id, item_id, quantity_needed, order_date, status
)
VALUES (
  301, 101, 100, CURRENT_DATE, 'Pending'
);



🎁 Assemble a Kit
INSERT INTO Kit (kit_id, kit_name)
VALUES (401, 'Hygiene Kit');

INSERT INTO Kit_Item (kit_id, item_id, quantity_per_kit)
VALUES (401, 101, 1); -- 1 toothbrush per kit



📍 Log a Distribution Event
INSERT INTO Distribution_Event (
  event_id, event_date, method_id, location_id, user_id
)
VALUES (
  501, '2025-08-27', 1, 2, 10
);


Log distributed items:
INSERT INTO Distribution_Log (
  item_id, quantity_distributed, distribution_date, event_id
)
VALUES (
  101, 25, '2025-08-27', 501
);
